Entry Type: Engineering Decision
Task Worked On: Return type/parameters for dfs()
Issue or decision: Comment was left and I had to decide what type of return and parameters
to use before writing logic
What I tried: Thought about using void with a bool & found parameter from main(),this would
let the DFS signal succeed without a return value. This meant adding a extra variable and passing it
through each time the recursive was called.
Final Decision: Used bool as the return type. This is because when the exit is found the function would
return true and the value travels back up the call stack. Also passed maze as a constant reference since the
DFS is the only thing that reads it. visited, parent_r, and parent_c passed by reference since DFS writes them
and exit_r and exit_c as plain ints because the exit coordinates never change.
Commit: Implemented dfs() logic

